Governor Okezie Ikpeazu of Abia State has approved the appointment of Mr. Christopher C. Osuagwu as Acting Executive Secretary of the Secondary Education Management Board (SEMB). The appointment was contained in a press statement issued by the Secretary to the State Government, SSG, Barrister Chris Ezem, Thursday. The statement said, “Until this appointment, Mr. Osuagwu was the Deputy Executive Secretary of SEMB, Aba Zone. “This appointment is with immediate effect”. In the same vein, Governor Okezie Ikpeazu has also approved the composition of the Secondary Education Management Board. Chief Eke Onyeforo is named as Chairman of the Management Board. Members of the Board were; Dr. Ogbonnaya Ememe, Sir Ishmael Olewe, Mrs Pauline Anyanwu, Dr. Sunny Orie, Dr. Mrs Nwakaego Uwadi and Executive Secretary, SEMB.